		<item>
		<title>Pulver launches Bellster</title>
		<link>http://werblog.com/2005/01/pulver-launches-bellster/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 22 Jan 2005 12:22:43 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kwerb]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[VOIP]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://werbach.com/wordpress/?p=1168</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[It worked for music file sharing&#8230; can it work for telephony? VOIP pioneer Jeff Pulver has announced Bellster, a peer-to-peer non-commercial phone network. You allow people to make VOIP calls that terminate through your public switched telephone network connection, in return for the ability to do the same. This will be an interesting experiment to ...<a class="post-readmore" href="http://werblog.com/2005/01/pulver-launches-bellster/">read more</a>]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>It worked for music file sharing&#8230; can it work for telephony?</p>
<p>VOIP pioneer Jeff Pulver has <a href="http://pulverblog.pulver.com/archives/001615.html">announced Bellster</a>, a peer-to-peer non-commercial phone network.  You allow people to make VOIP calls that terminate through your public switched telephone network connection, in return for the ability to do the same.</p>
<p>This will be an interesting experiment to watch.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>Whole-house VOIP: It&#039;s about time</title>
		<link>http://werblog.com/2005/01/whole-house-voip-its-about-time/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 22 Jan 2005 12:20:15 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kwerb]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[VOIP]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://werbach.com/wordpress/?p=1167</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[I&#8217;ve been waiting for a product like this. It&#8217;s an IP phone with built-in wireless connectivity to remote handsets. That means your voice over broadband connection will automatically support phones throughout your house, a key element in making residential VOIP ubiquitous.]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I&#8217;ve been waiting for a product like <a href="http://voxilla.com/modules.php?op=modload&#038;name=News&#038;file=article&#038;sid=135">this</a>.  It&#8217;s an IP phone with built-in wireless connectivity to remote handsets.  That means your voice over broadband connection will automatically support phones throughout your house, a key element in making residential VOIP ubiquitous.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>FCC starts VOIP proceeding</title>
		<link>http://werblog.com/2004/03/fcc-starts-voip-proceeding/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 11 Mar 2004 17:29:12 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kwerb]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[VOIP]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://werbach.com/wordpress/?p=1119</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[The FCC has released its notice of proposed rulemaking on voice over IP.&#160; The initial round of comments are due 60 days after the notice is published in the Federal Register, which is usually a few days after the official release.&#160;]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The FCC has released its <a href="http://hraunfoss.fcc.gov/edocs_public/attachmatch/FCC-04-28A1.pdf">notice of proposed rulemaking </a>on<br />
voice over IP.&nbsp; The initial round of comments are due 60 days<br />
after the notice is published in the Federal Register, which is usually<br />
a few days after the official release.&nbsp; </p>
]]></content:encoded>
